<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA'S WATER PROBLEMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Metropolitan Water District water rationing plan will take effect in 
February (Part A, Dec. 12). I hope that, before imposing local rationing and 
penalties for overuse, Mayor Bradley, the City Council and the county Board of 
Supervisors will remember to rescind (or cancel if still pending) the permits 
for Playa Vista, Porter Ranch, the Farmer's Market development, the Marina 
Triangle, the UCLA expansion and all the hundreds of other huge extravagant 
projects now on the books and approved or pending. 
</P>
<P>
All of them would use millions of gallons of water, require hundreds of 
thousands of new sewer hookups to an already overburdened system and produce 
insane additions to traffic congestion. Even now we have no extra water, no 
more room on streets and freeways, and certainly not enough clean air to go 
around. 
</P>
<P>
ALICE MCGAUGHEY 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
