<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: PORT HUENEME; 
</P>
<P>
SEARCHERS UNABLE TO FIND DIVER, 27 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ADRIANNE GOODMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
U.S. Coast Guard and Navy officials suspended at sundown Sunday a search for a 
scuba diver reported missing from a boat four miles off Port Hueneme. 
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old Oregon man, whose identity was not released pending 
notification of relatives, was with friends on a 26-foot pleasure boat when he 
made the dive about 11:30 a.m., apparently to search for pieces of a sunken 
boat in 80 feet of water, said Petty Officer Robert Beals of the Coast Guard's 
Long Beach station. 
</P>
<P>
The man's diving tank contained enough air for a 30-minute dive, Beals said. A 
companion on the boat sent out a distress signal when the diver failed to 
surface after 1 1/2 hours, Coast Guard officials said. 
</P>
<P>
A Coast Guard helicopter and two cutters were joined by a helicopter from the 
Point Mugu naval station in the search, which was hampered by three- to 
four-foot waves and winds up to 25 knots, Beals said. 
</P>
<P>
Coast Guard Petty Officer Jim Schweikhardt said officials "searched the area 
thoroughly and we couldn't locate him." There were no plans to resume the 
search today, he said. ADRIANNE GOODMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
