BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Golden State Ranked First: California is the headquarters for more 
industry-leading American companies than any other state in the nation, 
according to an annual survey by Forbes magazine. 
</P>
<P>
Forbes ranked 1,177 companies in 20 industries according to their five-year 
average return on equity. California took over the top spot with 11 companies 
ranked No. 1, five more than last year. New York State slipped to second with 
six. New York City remained the top headquarters city, with Los Angeles and 
Chicago tied for second place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
