allegedly stabbing another man to death after a quarrel in Reseda, Los Angeles 
police reported today. 
</P>
<P>
Police arrested William Scott Manciano on Sunday night after they found him 
hiding under a car behind a restaurant in the 19600 block of Sherman Way, Lt. 
Richard Pooler said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, a 22-year-old Reseda man whose name will not released until his 
relatives have been notified, staggered into the restaurant looking for help 
after the stabbing. He was taken to Northridge Hospital Medical Center where he 
died, Pooler said. 
</P>
