</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 13-year-old girl was recovering today from bullet wounds sustained on a 
Brooklyn street when a masked gunman opened fire on her and two friends because 
he wanted their nylon jackets, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The violence brought to 10 the number of people shot over a coat in the New 
York area since the beginning of the month, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Five of those people have died. 
</P>
<P>
The girl suffered a bullet wound to the thigh. 
</P>
<P>
She and two of her friends were accosted by a ski-mask clad gunman and an 
accomplice as the trio walked down a street in Brownsville, Police Sgt. Grace 
Ridley said. 
</P>
<P>
The girls initially refused the robbers' demands for their nylon jackets -- 
which had the word Columbia on them -- but two of them finally relented after 
the armed bandit fired a shot in the air. As the two robbers fled, the gunman 
randomly fired three more shots, one of which hit the 13-year-old girl. 
</P>
