<HEADLINE>
<P>
DANCING SOLO EASILY WINS DURAZNA STAKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taking the lead approaching the final turn, Dancing Solo romped to an 
eight-length victory Sunday in the 36th running of the $47,700 Durazna Stakes 
at Hawthorne Race Course. 
</P>
<P>
One Smooth Dancer and Amanda Kem, both longshots, finished second and third, 
respectively, in the one-mile, 70-yard race for 2-year-old fillies. 
</P>
<P>
The Missouri-bred Simply So, unbeaten in her first three races and the 6-5 
favorite, finished ninth in the field of 14. 
</P>
<P>
Ridden by Kerwin Clark, Dancing Solo paid $9.50, $4.60 and $3.40 and was timed 
in 1:44.35. The Kentucky-bred daughter of Rare Perfumer earned $28,620 for 
owner David Levitch to boost her total to $104,116. She has won four of five 
starts, including the recent Gowell Stakes at Turfway park in Florence, Ky. 
</P>
</TEXT>
