<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL POLL; 
</P>
<P>
LA. TECH ENDS 12-YEAR TOP 10 STREAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Long Beach was ranked 15th in this week's Associated Press women's 
college basketball poll, and Louisiana Tech ended its 12-year run in the Top 
10. 
</P>
<P>
At the top of the poll, Virginia (8-0) and North Carolina State (7-0) 
maintained their 1-2 positions. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach (5-2) maintained its position from the previous week's rankings. 
</P>
<P>
Louisiana Tech (3-2) fell from seventh to 11th today after losing to UNLV a 
week ago, 84-77. UNLV (7-0) moved from 14th to edge the Techsters for the 10th 
spot with 791 points to 776 points. Tech was also hurt by defending 
NCAA-champion Stanford's upset of then-No. 3 Georgia, 82-79, in The Cardinal's 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
